    "(7) MRR (mean reciprocal rank).",
    "MRR metric calculates the mean of the reciprocal position at which the first relevant method is found.",
    "(8) Hit-N. Hit-N is a metric designed for multi-defects, which measures the number of bugs that the predicted set contains at least N faulty statements.Table 15 [505][506][507][508][509][510][511][512][513][514][515][516][517][518][519][521][522][523]530,531] summarizes the commonly used metrics.",
